In the last complete year of data (2015; http://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/10665/250142/1/WER9138.pdf), WHO reported a total of 172 454 cases worldwide in 42 countries. This continuing cholera disaster in Yemen is only 12 weeks old and is now more than twice the whole of 2015's total number of cases and more than the peak year of the Haiti outbreak (2011) of 340 311 cases. - Mod.LL

